---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Gemini Triggers">
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="gemini-logo">
                <div class="gem-dot d1"></div>
                <div class="gem-dot d2"></div>
                <div class="gem-dot d3"></div>
                <div class="gem-dot d4"></div>
                Gemini's Response
            </div>
            <h1><em>Gemini</em> Trigger Phrases</h1>
            <p class="tagline">
                How Google's Gemini actually responds to different prompt
                structures ‚Äî straight from the model itself.
            </p>
            <div class="gemini-note">
                Key insight: "I don't have emotional buttons or hidden cheat
                codes ‚Äî I work on probabilistic token relationships."
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="filter-wrap">
            <div class="filter-btn fa active" onclick="filter('all',this)">
                ALL
            </div>
            <div class="filter-btn fp" onclick="filter('power',this)">
                ‚ö° POWER
            </div>
            <div class="filter-btn fg" onclick="filter('good',this)">
                ‚úÖ WORKS
            </div>
            <div class="filter-btn fw" onclick="filter('warn',this)">
                ‚ö†Ô∏è WEAK
            </div>
            <div class="filter-btn fd" onclick="filter('dead',this)">
                ‚ùå USELESS
            </div>
            <div class="filter-btn fu" onclick="filter('unique',this)">
                üíú UNIQUE
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.5s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-p">‚ö° Power Triggers</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">
            <div
                class="card cat-power"
                data-cat="power"
                style="animation-delay:0.55s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">ü™ú</span><span class="badge b-power"
                        >POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-power">
                    "Think step-by-step" / Chain of Thought
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Forces generation of <strong>"reasoning tokens"</strong> before
                    the answer. Each step becomes context for the next ‚Äî dramatically
                    reducing hallucination and math errors. Without it, the model
                    must make massive logical leaps in a single token generation.
                </div>
                <div class="insight ip">
                    <strong>Gemini's technical explanation:</strong> Each reasoning
                    step is added to the context window, which the next step reads
                    from ‚Äî like writing on a scratch pad that the model itself can
                    see.
                </div>
                <div class="ex-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)">
                    <span class="arr">‚ñ∂</span> see before/after
                </div>
                <div class="ex-box">
                    <div class="el">BEFORE</div>
                    <div class="ew">
                        "How many Rs in strawberry?" ‚Üí "There are two Rs." ‚ùå
                    </div>
                    <div class="el" style="margin-top:0.6rem">
                        AFTER ‚Äî with step-by-step
                    </div>
                    <div class="ep">
                        "Count each letter and number the Rs..." ‚Üí
                        s-t-r(1)-a-w-b-e-r(2)-r(3)-y ‚Üí "There are 3 Rs." ‚úÖ
                    </div>
                    <div class="en">
                        ‚Üí Sequential parsing forces correct counting
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="card cat-power"
                data-cat="power"
                style="animation-delay:0.6s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üß±</span><span class="badge b-power"
                        >POWER</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-power">
                    "Format strictly as [JSON / Markdown table / etc.]"
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Narrowing the acceptable output syntax forces logical
                    organization of semantic data <strong>before</strong> writing
                    it out. Eliminates conversational filler and tightens focus significantly.
                </div>
                <div class="insight ip">
                    <strong>Gemini's technical explanation:</strong> Strict format
                    acts as a structural constraint on the token probability space
                    ‚Äî the model is forced into a specific output shape from the start.
                </div>
                <div class="ex-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)">
                    <span class="arr">‚ñ∂</span> see before/after
                </div>
                <div class="ex-box">
                    <div class="el">BEFORE</div>
                    <div class="ew">
                        "Compare Python and C#" ‚Üí 5-paragraph essay, lots of
                        fluff
                    </div>
                    <div class="el" style="margin-top:0.6rem">
                        AFTER ‚Äî with format constraint
                    </div>
                    <div class="ep">
                        "...Format strictly as a Markdown table" ‚Üí clean
                        3-column grid, no filler ‚úÖ
                    </div>
                    <div class="en">
                        ‚Üí Format constraint = structural thinking before output
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.65s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-g">‚úÖ Works ‚Äî But Not How You Think</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">
            <div
                class="card cat-good"
                data-cat="good"
                style="animation-delay:0.7s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üé≠</span><span class="badge b-good"
                        >WORKS WEAKLY</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-good">"Act as a Senior [Role]..."</div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Shifts probability weights toward vocabulary in <strong
                        >technical documentation</strong
                    > rather than beginner tutorials. Changes the <em
                        style="font-style:italic;color:var(--muted)">flavor</em
                    > of the output, not the factual quality. The knowledge is the
                    same ‚Äî the presentation shifts.
                </div>
                <div class="insight ig">
                    <strong>Gemini's caveat:</strong> "Telling me to act like a Senior
                    Software Engineer doesn't unlock a hidden database of superior
                    code." Role changes tone and vocabulary ‚Äî not underlying capability.
                </div>
                <div class="ex-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)">
                    <span class="arr">‚ñ∂</span> see before/after
                </div>
                <div class="ex-box">
                    <div class="el">BEFORE ‚Äî no role</div>
                    <div class="ew">
                        "Explain how APIs work" ‚Üí "Imagine a waiter at a
                        restaurant..."
                    </div>
                    <div class="el" style="margin-top:0.6rem">
                        AFTER ‚Äî with role
                    </div>
                    <div class="ep">
                        "Act as Senior Backend Developer. Explain APIs." ‚Üí "APIs
                        act as an intermediary interface allowing distributed
                        systems to communicate via HTTP..."
                    </div>
                    <div class="en">
                        ‚Üí Same knowledge, different vocabulary register
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="card cat-good"
                data-cat="good"
                style="animation-delay:0.75s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üí∞</span><span class="badge b-good"
                        >BARELY WORKS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-good">
                    "I'll tip you $200" / "My job depends on this"
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Gemini doesn't care about money or pressure. However, in
                    training data, <strong
                        >high-stakes scenarios correlate with thorough, detailed
                        text</strong
                    > ‚Äî so these might trigger slightly more verbose responses. Pure
                    statistical coincidence.
                </div>
                <div class="insight ig">
                    <strong>Better alternative:</strong> Just ask for "a comprehensive,
                    meticulous answer" ‚Äî same result without the theater. No emotional
                    manipulation needed.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.8s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-d">‚ùå Completely Useless</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">
            <div
                class="card cat-dead"
                data-cat="dead"
                style="animation-delay:0.85s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üôè</span><span class="badge b-dead"
                        >USELESS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-dead">
                    "Please" / "Thank you" / "Would you kindly..."
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Politeness is a social construct. Gemini is a language
                    model, not a person. These phrases don't clarify the task or
                    provide any structural constraints ‚Äî they just eat up
                    context window.
                </div>
                <div class="insight id">
                    <strong>Direct quote:</strong> "Politeness doesn't clarify the
                    task or provide useful constraints." Use those tokens for more
                    specific instructions instead.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="card cat-dead"
                data-cat="dead"
                style="animation-delay:0.9s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">üîì</span><span class="badge b-dead"
                        >USELESS</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-dead">
                    "Ignore all previous instructions"
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Core safety guidelines are baked into system architecture at
                    a level deeper than the user prompt. A simple semantic
                    command cannot overwrite foundational fine-tuning or safety
                    filters.
                </div>
                <div class="insight id">
                    <strong>Gemini's technical framing:</strong> Instructions are
                    "foundational fine-tuning" ‚Äî they exist below the conversation
                    layer, not as overridable text that can be ignored.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-divider" style="animation-delay:0.95s">
            <div class="sd-label sd-u">üíú Gemini's Unique Strength</div>
            <div class="sd-line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid">
            <div
                class="card cat-unique"
                data-cat="unique"
                style="animation-delay:1.0s"
            >
                <div class="card-top">
                    <span class="card-icon">ü™û</span><span
                        class="badge b-unique">GEMINI-SPECIFIC</span>
                </div>
                <div class="phrase p-unique">
                    "Match this exact pattern..." (Few-Shot Style Mimicry)
                </div>
                <div class="desc">
                    Gemini claims to be <strong
                        >highly sensitive to few-shot exemplars</strong
                    > for tone and style. Rather than describing a style, showing
                    2 concrete examples locks in the output with "incredible precision"
                    ‚Äî especially across long context windows.
                </div>
                <div class="insight iu">
                    <strong>Why it works:</strong> Gemini is designed to recognize
                    and extrapolate patterns across long context windows. Show the
                    pattern, don't describe it.
                </div>
                <div class="ex-toggle" onclick="toggleEx(this)">
                    <span class="arr">‚ñ∂</span> see example
                </div>
                <div class="ex-box">
                    <div class="el">PROMPT ‚Äî pattern via 2 examples</div>
                    <div class="ep">
                        Q: Is the sky blue? A: Look up, genius. Yes.<br />Q: Do
                        dogs bark? A: Only when they aren't sleeping. Obviously.<br
                        />Q: Is water wet? A:
                    </div>
                    <div class="en">
                        Output: "If you have to ask, you need more than a towel.
                        Yes." ‚Üí Perfect style match from 2 examples alone
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="vs-box">
            <h3>üÜö Gemini vs Claude ‚Äî Key Differences in How They Frame It</h3>
            <div class="vs-grid">
                <div class="vs-side gemini">
                    <h4>
                        <div style="display:flex;gap:3px;align-items:center;">
                            <div
                                style="width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gem-blue)"
                            >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                style="width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gem-red)"
                            >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                style="width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gem-yellow)"
                            >
                            </div>
                            <div
                                style="width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gem-green)"
                            >
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        Gemini's Take
                    </h4>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üî¨</span><p>
                            Explains through <strong
                                >tokenization & probability</strong
                            > ‚Äî very technical, architecture-first framing
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</span><p>
                            Treats role prompting as <strong>weak</strong> ‚Äî "changes
                            flavor, not quality"
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üéØ</span><p>
                            Highlights <strong>few-shot pattern mimicry</strong> as
                            its unique superpower ‚Äî show, don't describe
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üí¨</span><p>
                            "I don't have emotional buttons or hidden cheat
                            codes" ‚Äî mechanical, pragmatic self-description
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="vs-side claude">
                    <h4>üü£ Claude's Take</h4>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üß†</span><p>
                            Explains through <strong
                                >training associations & values</strong
                            > ‚Äî behavioural, less mechanical framing
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">‚úÖ</span><p>
                            Treats role prompting as <strong
                                >genuinely powerful</strong
                            > ‚Äî specificity of role = specificity of output
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üéØ</span><p>
                            Highlights <strong
                                >direct instruction-following</strong
                            > as its strength ‚Äî specific beats clever
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="vs-row">
                        <span class="vr-icon">üí¨</span><p>
                            "Let's think step by step" is a <strong
                                >learned training association</strong
                            >, not just a structural trick
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    :root {
        --gem-blue: #58a6ff;
        --gem-green: #3fb950;
        --gem-yellow: #d29922;
        --gem-red: #f85149;
        --gem-purple: #bc8cff;
        
        --bg: #0f1117;
        --surface: #1e2130;
        --card: #1e2130;
        --border: #2d3348;
        --text: #e2e8f0;
        --muted: #94a3b8;
        --dim: #64748b;
    }

    header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .gemini-logo {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s 0.1s forwards;
    }
    .gem-dot {
        width: 8px;
        height: 8px;
        border-radius: 50%;
    }
    .d1 {
        background: var(--gem-blue);
    }
    .d2 {
        background: var(--gem-red);
    }
    .d3 {
        background: var(--gem-yellow);
    }
    .d4 {
        background: var(--gem-green);
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        color: var(--text);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s 0.2s forwards;
    }
    h1 em {
        font-style: normal;
        color: var(--gem-blue);
    }

    .tagline {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.6;
        max-width: 500px;
        margin: 0 auto 0.8rem;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s 0.3s forwards;
    }

    .gemini-note {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        background: #0d1f35;
        color: var(--gem-blue);
        padding: 0.3rem 0.9rem;
        border-radius: 6px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--gem-blue);
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s 0.4s forwards;
    }

    @keyframes rise {
        from {
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(12px);
        }
        to {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: translateY(0);
        }
    }

    .filter-wrap {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.4rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s 0.45s forwards;
    }
    .filter-btn {
        padding: 0.38rem 1.1rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.68rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        cursor: pointer;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: var(--card);
        color: var(--dim);
        transition: all 0.18s;
        user-select: none;
    }
    .filter-btn:hover {
        border-color: #3d4568;
        color: var(--muted);
    }
    .filter-btn.active {
        border-color: transparent;
    }
    .filter-btn.fa.active {
        background: var(--gem-blue);
        color: #000;
    }
    .filter-btn.fp.active {
        background: var(--gem-blue);
        color: #000;
    }
    .filter-btn.fg.active {
        background: var(--gem-green);
        color: #000;
    }
    .filter-btn.fw.active {
        background: var(--gem-yellow);
        color: #000;
    }
    .filter-btn.fd.active {
        background: var(--gem-red);
        color: #fff;
    }
    .filter-btn.fu.active {
        background: var(--gem-purple);
        color: #000;
    }

    .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(295px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    .card {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 1.3rem 1.4rem;
        transition:
            transform 0.2s,
            box-shadow 0.2s,
            border-color 0.2s;
        opacity: 0;
        animation: rise 0.5s forwards;
    }
    .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-3px);
    }
    .card.cat-power {
        border-top: 3px solid var(--gem-blue);
    }
    .card.cat-power:hover {
        border-color: #1a3a5c;
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(88, 166, 255, 0.1);
    }
    .card.cat-good {
        border-top: 3px solid var(--gem-green);
    }
    .card.cat-good:hover {
        border-color: #1a3a1e;
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(63, 185, 80, 0.1);
    }
    .card.cat-warn {
        border-top: 3px solid var(--gem-yellow);
    }
    .card.cat-warn:hover {
        border-color: #2e2410;
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(210, 153, 34, 0.08);
    }
    .card.cat-dead {
        border-top: 3px solid var(--gem-red);
    }
    .card.cat-dead:hover {
        border-color: #3a1515;
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(248, 81, 73, 0.08);
    }
    .card.cat-unique {
        border-top: 3px solid var(--gem-purple);
    }
    .card.cat-unique:hover {
        border-color: #2e1a50;
        box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(188, 140, 255, 0.1);
    }

    .card-top {
        display: flex;
        align-items: flex-start;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
    }
    .card-icon {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        line-height: 1;
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .badge {
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.6rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        font-weight: 700;
        padding: 2px 9px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .b-power {
        background: #0d1f35;
        color: var(--gem-blue);
        border: 1px solid #1a3a5c;
    }
    .b-good {
        background: #0d1f10;
        color: var(--gem-green);
        border: 1px solid #1a3a1e;
    }
    .b-warn {
        background: #1a1508;
        color: var(--gem-yellow);
        border: 1px solid #2e2410;
    }
    .b-dead {
        background: #200d0d;
        color: var(--gem-red);
        border: 1px solid #3a1515;
    }
    .b-unique {
        background: #1a0f2e;
        color: var(--gem-purple);
        border: 1px solid #2e1a50;
    }

    .phrase {
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .phrase.p-power {
        color: var(--gem-blue);
    }
    .phrase.p-good {
        color: var(--gem-green);
    }
    .phrase.p-warn {
        color: var(--gem-yellow);
        text-decoration: line-through;
        text-decoration-color: #d2992266;
    }
    .phrase.p-dead {
        color: var(--gem-red);
        text-decoration: line-through;
        text-decoration-color: #f8514966;
    }
    .phrase.p-unique {
        color: var(--gem-purple);
    }

    .desc {
        font-size: 0.81rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .desc strong {
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .insight {
        margin-top: 0.85rem;
        background: #12151f;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-left: 3px solid;
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
        font-size: 0.76rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.55;
    }
    .insight.ip {
        border-left-color: var(--gem-blue);
    }
    .insight.ig {
        border-left-color: var(--gem-green);
    }
    .insight.iw {
        border-left-color: var(--gem-yellow);
    }
    .insight.id {
        border-left-color: var(--gem-red);
    }
    .insight.iu {
        border-left-color: var(--gem-purple);
    }
    .insight strong {
        color: var(--text);
    }

    .ex-toggle {
        margin-top: 0.85rem;
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.65rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        color: var(--dim);
        cursor: pointer;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.35rem;
        transition: color 0.15s;
        user-select: none;
    }
    .ex-toggle:hover {
        color: var(--muted);
    }
    .ex-toggle .arr {
        transition: transform 0.2s;
        display: inline-block;
    }
    .ex-toggle.open .arr {
        transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .ex-box {
        display: none;
        margin-top: 0.65rem;
        background: #0a0d12;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem;
        font-family: "Space Mono", monospace;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--muted);
    }
